Class DeclarationNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.fathomsoft.fathom.tree.TreeNode

  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ClassNode, FieldNode, MethodNode

    public class DeclarationNode
extends VariableNode
    VariableNode extension that represents the declaration of a variable or method. Contains the modifiers for visibility and whether or not the variable/method is static.
    Since:
    v0.1 Jan 5, 2014 at 9:10:49 PM
    Version:
    v0.2 Apr 2, 2014 at 6:53:41 PM
    Author:
    Braden Steffaniak

      • isStatic

        public boolean isStatic()
        Get whether or not the specified DeclarationNode is static. Static variables/methods are shared among each of its containing class's instances.
        Returns:
        Whether or not the specified DeclarationNode is static.

      • getStaticText

        public java.lang.String getStaticText()
        (WARNING: CURRENTLY ONLY RETURNS "static")
        Get the text that is associated with the static value of the specified DeclarationNode.

        For example: If static is true, the method will return "static" if it is not, it will return an empty String.
        Returns:
        The value representing the static value.

      • setStatic
